<Author>lexycal
<Content>Split decision We stayed at the Husa Barcelona from May 20 - May 25th 2007.For the price of the room you expect a doorman to at least help with the bags...nope. The front desk people were friendly enough and helpfull with tourist information although the morning front desk mananger seemed to have a really bad attitude most days. It was really nice that the hotel offered breakfast each morning from 7am-11am free of charge. Great location to all shops and La Ramblas (great tourist walk).The bad part was the room. It looked much better in the pictures on the website. You could hear the people on the balcony clear as a bell in your room. The doors are pretty thin as well. Oh and don't let me forget the bed bugs. From the first day to the last they got worse. My arms were eaten alive. I really didn't know what was bitting me at first because it was one or two bumps. By the end of the week my entire forearm was a mess. Upon checkout I told the front desk person and guess what.. for the first time it seemed they didn't understand english. Word for the wise when traveling remove all covers from the bed and request new ones. All in all not a bad place to stay. 
