<Author>pinkilili
<Content>Location good, otherwise only ok I stayed a few nights at the Husa Barcelona with my hubby. The room was spacious, on the top floor, with a nice little balcony. The decor was very neutral, your average hotel style, didn't make an impression. The biggest problem was the bathroom which smelled damp and mouldy - it was an extremely strong smell, which really had an effect on the atmosphere of the room. In the end we decided to change hotels.The lift didn't always work but I'm not complaining since walking the staris is good excersice :)The breakfast was nice, you'll be ready to tackle the sights after it.The service at the front desk was friendly and we were always greeted with a smile.Husa Barcelona is located right in the city center on a quiet side street. It's a walking distance from almost all the interesting sights and there's a metro station close by. Check out the small bar right opposite the hotel if you want to stay away from the really touristy bars :) No English was spoken there but don't worry, you'll get your point across!Barcelona is such a wonderful city with so much to see that you won't be spending much time in the hotel, so locationwise I'd say go for the Husa but if it's atmosphere you're after - forget it! 
