<Author>Sue60
<Content>Good location We liked this hotel,(24-28 March 2007). It's so well located near the top of La Rambla, we walked to the cathedral, Casa Battlo, Casa Milia, the sea, Palau de la Musica. The staff were pleasant  helpful  spoke English as I'm ashamed to say we only had a few words of Spanish/Catalan between us.We were on the 7th floor  our rooms had outdoor terraces with chairs  tables. Our friends in 707  710 had a good view over Placa de Catalunya but we had asked for a quiet room so were put further along the street, away from the busy square. The double glazing was good so the rooms were quiet . They were comfortable  clean with a pleasant breakfast room.There was a buffet of fresh  tinned fruit (this could have been a bit more imaginative),4 types of cereal, yoghurt,cold meats, cheeses, breads, hard boiled eggs, scrambled egg, bacon  sausage, various delicious looking croissants  pastries.So plenty of choice.We'd have used the terrace more if the weather had been warmer,as there's a great market about 10-15 minute walk away off la Rambla so you could buy lovely fruit etc. If your room doesn't have its own there is another terrace with tables  chairs on the 7th floor.It was a good base  we got the 4th night free, booking with Expedia. We'd certainly consider this one again if we go back  there's lots to do  see that we didn't have time for.Do look after your money  cards in Barcelona. Our friend who travelled separately from us had her purse taken from the bottom of her zipped-up bag that was over her shoulder, at the bus station as soon as she arrived. At the police station she met someone else who had her bag taken when she put it down to get her case out of the bus,  at the hotel was someone else who had something taken while she was out. My neighbour had her bag snatched from off her shoulder last year. It's worth having a bag or camera on a long strap that can go across your body  you can hold it on the front, with the opening on the inside.I had small amounts of money in different zip pockets in my bag  in a body belt,  didn't take a purse. The hotel room had a safe, 10 euro returnable deposit for the key.Don't be put off going to Barcelona though, hope you have a lovely time. 
