<Content>Excellent Location We have just got back from a mini-break , 3 nights in Barcelona. When we arrived at this hotel the staff were helpful. We were welcomed and given our key to our room. Our first expression was this wasn't a 4 star hotel. The size of the rooms were spacious enough, the decor was a bit let down. The bathroom and W.C was separate. The hotel maids were very good, cleaned rooms everyday, clean towels available everyday and also changed our bedding in the duration of our stay. The location was excellent as it was very accessible to the centre of catylan square and fanstatic shops located near by. Plenty of restaurants within walking distance. We had arrived by taxi as we weren;t sure of location, but travelling back we took the Airport bus which is literally few minutes walking distance from the hotel and it only cost 3.75 euro's per person. This was our second visit to the beautiful city and I can say the location was perfect. We had breakfast booked separately which we stayed for one morning. Many choices available. The beds were comfortable but we found it was it abit noisy with traffic late at night and early in the morining which woke us up. There was a mini-bar available but no coffee facilities in the room. Not to worry as there plenty of coffee houses located near by, and one across the road. There is also a theatre across the road, we were lucky we had a room with trees giving us privacy from the bright lights. I would recommend this hotel for it's location and average cost 拢70 for the night. 
