<Content>Good hotel, Excellent location We spent 5 days at Husa Barcelona hotel for a family vacation. The room was big enouch with 2 beds combined to a double bed and one bed for the child. The room was clean and the bathroom was well equipped. We had a nice balcony facing the street and a minibar that we did not use. On the downside there was no English channel on the TV. Even the CNN was in Spanish, and a coffee maker in the room could be a nice addition. The breakfast that was included in our rate was just excellent. It included 3 types of fresh juice and a nice choice of hot drinks. Eggs, bacon and sausages, a selection of cheeses and cold meats, vegetables and fruits, cereals and excellent morning pastry and cakes. The staff was very friendly. On top of all that- the location of this hotel, right at the Place de Catalunya, is just great. It is a minute of walking from many good restaurants, bars and shops as well as a metro station. Very convenient to take a short rest after walking down Ramblas avenues. We would certainly recommend this hotel to friends going to Barcelona. 
