<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Good Value, Good Location  I don't know what some people expect, but I found it excellent value for money. We paid 拢516 for a twin room for five nights - it was recommended by a travel agent - a proper travel agent not just one who hands out brochures.We were a bit surprised at the minute size of the reception area having looked on the web site it looked quite spacious. One of the young men behind the desk took our cases - perhaps because we were two ladies on our own - put them in the lift and we set off to our room.The lighting system is rather eccenric, every time we turned something on we turned something off, but it just amused us.The bathroom was small with over the bath shower and vanity unit with a big mirror and excellent lighting - handy for make up etc and a hair dryer.A plus point was the separate loo and bidet across from the bathroom, very rare for a hotel of this size.It was just a minute from Placa Catalunya with buses and Metro close by plus El Corte Ingles department store which to us spoiled Londoners didn't have any of the style we are used to.We asked the receptionist on the first night to recommend a restaurant fairly close by and he suggested one about 20 years away which was excellent Catalan food. He didn't give us a card or tell us to say Jose sent us so that he would get a kickback.The breakfast was very good with plenty of choice of breads, cakes, cereals, jam, honey, ham, cheese even olives! Tea was a bit weak but we had taken the precaution of bringing a few English tea bags with us. There was bacon and scrambled egg for those who have to have the hot breakfast.On the morning of our departure we struggled down to the mezzanine level with our suitcases - one of the guys came out from behind the desk and said we should have left them in the room and they would have fetched them later. he luggage room was full, we went back after lunch to get our bags, they ordered a taxi for us and took our bags out to the taxi.We did wonder on our first evening where the bar might be, but as there was a very nice little bar bang across the street, it didn;t really seem to be a problem. They have conference facilities there - maybe the bar is opened then.We seemed to have had a totally different experience from others with the staff, but the Spanish are a sort of insular race they are not like th Italians who always want to make a fuss of you.Another point unless you are paying top dollar you are always going to find city hotels in Europe small - I have stayed in dozens of hotels all around Europe and for value for money and pleasant service - I would rate the Husa Barcelona quite highlyPerhaps some times if you approach the staff in a courteous way they will be more courteous and helpful to you.A FREQUENT TRAVELLER LONDON 
