<Content>Location, location Location is the only thing this hotel, as a four star hotel, has got going for it. After budgeting our way around Europe we decided to stay somewhere a little more posh to end our trip as we were flying home from Barcelona. I've stayed at 4 star hotels before and the facilities here were most definately not 4 star. We booked through the tourist office at Catalunya Square when we arrived and got the last minute price of 120 euro per night although they wanted to charge us 170 euro for the second night.The rooms were clean and quiet but the lighting was hilarious. If the bathroom light wouldn't swith on, you'd have to go over and turn on the bedside lamp, then go back and hit the bathroom light again. It was a game of lottery as to what light would come on when you hit a switch.One thing that really annoyed me was that having booked a double room we found that the bed was actually 2 singles pushed together with seperate blankets. I echo other reviewer's comments about the mysterious bar/restaurant. I looked around before asking at reception where the bar was only to be told there wasn't one. Why on earth would you have a sign saying bar  restaurant on level 1 if you haven't got one???Location brilliant, staff unhelpful, rooms a theme park. Who hands out the star ratings in spain? If you can get a bargain price, consider it but if they are looking for anything near 170 euro, forget it. 
