<Content>Ideally placed In terms of the facilities this is not a 4 Star hotel, I think it may struggle to get 3 Stars in the UK. However if you can pick up a good deal then it is in a great location. Whilst the decor is basic the rooms are of a good size and ours had the toilet seperate from the bathroom which was useful. The air conditioning was very good and combined with the higly sound-proof glazing allowed for some lazy lie-ins.The staff were friendly and efficient in their jobs. After one of my companions came in slightly worse for wear one evening he was trying to get the night porter to teach him some Spanish. The next day there was an envelope waiting for him with print outs of a number of handy phrases, which we felt was a nice touch.It was a bit disappointing that the bar was of the imaginery kind, but considering most places are open into the small hours anyway it wasn't a huge problem. There is also a cafe/bar just over the road which is ideal for a quick drink (and much better than waiting for people in the slightly cramped lobby).I would certainly still here again but wouldn't pay any more than the 拢70 per room per night that we did. 
