<Content>Great Location - Good for the Price Stayed for three nights and found the central location of the hotel excellent (just off the Passeig Gracia). The room was very clean and the service we received was fine.Room was fitted with everything you'd expect, ie, minibar, shower and bath, toilet and bidet, wardrobe etc. Decoration was on the sparse side, but considering the low price of the hotel this was fine by us. We also had a small balcony, which not all the rooms possess.The room had a safe, but you need to ask at reception for a key - this isn't automatically supplied.In response to other reviewers' comments, breakfast is not included in the room rate, but this is fairly standard in Barcelona. Also the complaint about the lack of tea and coffee making facilities is really unwarranted - I've never been in a continental hotel that DOES have these, it's more of an English tradition!Overall, it wasn't the most luxurious hotel we've ever stayed in, but for a city break it was fantastic, as you're out of your room for most of the time. There's plenty of coffee houses, bars, restaurants and nightlife on the doorstep and the metro station is literally 25 yards away (although you can't feel it rumbling underfoot!) 
