<Content>Great location but everything else was not so good... We stayed for 3 nights from 26 Dec 2004. The location of the hotel cannot be faulted, only a few minutes walk from La Ramblas and the heart of the city. But, we had read this was 4 star (ok, so self rated should always raise a question I guess), and from first impressions this was clearly not the case. The lobby is tiny, but there again, who needs a big lobby, so long as the rooms are ok. Check in done, we get the lift to the 5th floor.The halls and stairs are all marble, but once in the corridor, and then the room, this changes. The first thing we noticed in the room was the odd layout - starting with the double bed with one side against the wall. The bathroom was ok - good size, good shower, and fairly new, but why was it built so as to mean the bed was shoved into this cramped position?The decor of the room was tired, and the walls made of an extra thin rice paper so that when the maids started cleaning at some godforsaken hour in the morning, you got to hear every sound. Not much noise from outside - good glazing - but lots and lots from inside!There is a sign on the wall in the lobby to indicate a 'bar'. We looked; we didn't find. We asked; the receptionists looked puzzled and said they weren't sure if it was open (and didn't say where it was), but said we could get a meal in the restaurant. We went up again, and waited. And wandered about, and waited some more, but no-one ever came. We left and went out for tapas...Overall, we were disappointed. We got a fairly good deal on the room online, and maybe they save the old 5th floor rooms for the penny pinching Brits! Wouldn't recommend and wouldn't stay there again. But if you do, make sure they don't put you on floor 5! 
